ELECTRIC AUTO-LITE COMPANY, Petitioner, v. SECURITIES & EXCHANGE COMMISSION, Respondent. No. 7346. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. June 4, 1937. Larkin, Rathbone & Perry, of New York City, for petitioner. John J. Burns, Thomas J. Lynch, and Francis S. Walker, all of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before HICKS, SIMONS and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel, it is ordered that this cause be and the same is dismissed, without costs to either party as against the other.
